result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tauheed Lynell Graves in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
cab
This case was in Judge Kremers for the sentencing on the defendant's other case, 15CM683.  It was previously dismissed by the court.

Defendant Tauheed Lynell Graves in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Tauheed Lynell Graves in custody.  William T. Berens appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
AS TO COUNTS 1, 2 & 3
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion of the state, the court ordered Counts 1, 2 & 3 Dismissed, But Read In.  Other in-court activity (for review with sentencing) scheduled for September 10, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Tauheed J Graves in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Tauheed J Graves in custody.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for a Return of Doctor's Report. Report states that Dr. Collins of the Wisconsin Forensic Unit found that the defendant is competent to proceed. Parties do not contest findings of Dr. Collins. FInding the defendant competent to proceed court reinstated proceedings. State's motion for joinder GRANTED over the defense objection of cases 15CM683, 15CM953 & 14CM1134. Defense counsel requests case be set for Jury Trial.  Defendant enters a SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND as to case 15CM953. Court advised parties that all discovery must be turned over, all witness lists and motions filed 20 DAYS in advance of the Jury Trial date. All conditions of bail remain in effect. Court reinstated bail and all conditions. Case adjourned for Jury Trial to branch 23.  Jury trial scheduled for July 20, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Received & Filed, Wisconsin Forensic Unit Report.

Attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke in court, defendant Tauheed Lynell Graves not in court, in custody.  Molly M Schmidt for Ben Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant NOT produced. Defense counsel WAIVED appearance. State challenged defendant's competency to proceed in this matter for reasons placed on the record. Court Called 14CM1134 & 15CM683 to challenge competency on this pending cases before branch 23 not scheduled for today's hearing. Defense did not object.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court suspended proceedings and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.  Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department pending Doctor's Report Return. Case adjourned to branch 23  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for May 19, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms. Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings. Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Deona C. and Dawnette C.

Defendant Tauheed Lynell Graves in court with attorney Torrie R. Williams.  Defendant Tauheed Lynell Graves in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Grady, Branch 23.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for April 15, 2015 at 08:30 am.
